Q2ChatGPT >>> GA4 & GTM : Listener code  for text copied event.

✅ Step 1: Add Listener Code to the Page
This code listens for the copy event and pushes it into the GTM dataLayer:

<script>
  document.addEventListener('copy', function(event) {
    const copiedText = window.getSelection().toString().trim();

    if (copiedText) {
      window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
      window.dataLayer.push({
        event: 'text_copied',
        copied_text: copiedText
      });
    }
  });
</script>

✅ Step 2: In Google Tag Manager (GTM)
1. Trigger Setup
Go to Triggers → New
Trigger Type: Custom Event
Event Name: text_copied
Trigger fires on: All Custom Events
Name it: Text Copied Trigger

2. Variable Setup (Optional but Recommended)
Go to Variables → New
Type: Data Layer Variable
Name: copied_text
Data Layer Variable Name: copied_text

3. Tag Setup
Go to Tags → New
Tag Type: GA4 Event
Configuration Tag: (your GA4 configuration)
Event Name: text_copied
Parameters (optional but useful):
copied_text → {{copied_text}}

✅ Step 3: Publish the GTM Container
Once done, preview your site and copy any text. You should see the event in the Tag Assistant and later in GA4's Realtime > Events.









